columns.name: transit_gateway_id
columns.description: The ID of the transit gateway.

columns.name: transit_gateway_arn
columns.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the transit gateway.

columns.name: state
columns.description: The state of the transit gateway.

columns.name: owner_id
columns.description: The ID of the AWS account ID that owns the transit gateway.

columns.name: description
columns.description: The description of the transit gateway.

columns.name: creation_time
columns.description: The date and time when transit gateway was created.

columns.name: amazon_side_asn
columns.description: A private Autonomous System Number (ASN) for the Amazon side of a BGP session. The range is 64512 to 65534 for 16-bit ASNs and 4200000000 to 4294967294 for 32-bit ASNs.

columns.name: association_default_route_table_id
columns.description: The ID of the default association route table.

columns.name: auto_accept_shared_attachments
columns.description: Indicates whether attachment requests are automatically accepted.

columns.name: default_route_table_association
columns.description: Indicates whether resource attachments are automatically associated with the default association route table.

columns.name: default_route_table_propagation
columns.description: Indicates whether resource attachments are automatically associated with the default association route table.

columns.name: dns_support
columns.description: Indicates whether DNS support is enabled.

columns.name: multicast_support
columns.description: Indicates whether multicast is enabled on the transit gateway.

columns.name: propagation_default_route_table_id
columns.description: The ID of the default propagation route table.

columns.name: vpn_ecmp_support
columns.description: Indicates whether Equal Cost Multipath Protocol support is enabled.

columns.name: cidr_blocks
columns.description: A list of transit gateway CIDR blocks.

columns.name: tags_src
columns.description: A list of tags that are assigned to the transit gateway.
